You provide some of this data directly, such as when you order an Havnor product, contact customer support, or register for an Havnor event or publication. We also collect information into your interaction with Havnor® Services and our website, for example, using embedded product technologies and cookies. We also obtain data from third parties.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" accent_color="#dcdcdc"][vc_custom_heading text="2. If you visit one of our stores or locations, attend a trade show or event, or otherwise contact us, you may also voluntarily provide similar information. Interactive stories in some Havnor Services may allow you to invite friends, follow others, comment on or make unique posts, or share photos, video or other personal content. When you affirmatively share this content, we may collect and use it in accordance with this Notice. Additionally, by way of your social action, we may receive information about you from another user, such as when your friend posts content that includes you.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" accent_color="#dcdcdc"][vc_custom_heading text="3. Device and Product Operation" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:17px|text_align:left|color:%23333333|line_height:27px" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1539089704101{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]1.1 If you download and use certain Havnor Service like software or an app, we may track and collect usage data, such as when the software or app accesses our servers, what information and files have been downloaded through the use of the software or app, and how you interact with the software or app during use. Your home sensors communicate with the panel using encrypted low-power radio signals that don't require your Wi-Fi network.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Will my security work if my network goes?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Yes. Your system has 4G LTE cellular backup to make sure your home is still professionally monitored.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are wireless security systems secure?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Absolutely. It's much easier for an intruder to cut a landline than disrupt the wireless signal to the Alarm Response Center. If an intruder tries to break your security panel or base, it will set off an alarm before the system is compromised. Wireless sensors are also secure. Since they aren't constrained by phone lines or wall mounts, they can be placed out of view of intruders. If a sensor is tampered with, an alarm will be triggered as well.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can I turn the alarm system on and off?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Yes. You can use a passcode to arm and disarm it from the panel. You can also use the mobile app or a keychain remote.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="My system connected to automation devices?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]That's a popular option for many Brinks Home Security customers. Your system can serve as a hub for up to 119 Z-wave smart sensors and devices, such as video cameras, locks and lights. Compatible devices from multiple manufacturers can be controlled remotely from the mobile app.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Do pets trigger motion sensors?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]In general, only pets over 40 lbs. are capable of triggering motion sensors. To safeguard against pet-triggered alarms, we suggest following the recommendations provided with your security system, and (if possible) setting motion detectors in areas that pets don't normally frequent.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Why don't your systems include sensors?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Our door sensors can also be used as window sensors, though window sensors aren't cost-effective for home protection. Window break-ins are rare, and with the effective protection provided by well-placed door and motion sensors, window sensors are rarely necessary. If you absolutely need window sensors, just add extra door sensors when you purchase your system.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one" title_size="20px"][vc_accordion_tab title="When a security breach occurs?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Yes. Each sensor protects a door, window, or area, and will indicate the location of the breach when an alarm occurs.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Without good cellular service will system work?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Absolutely. Your system uses dual-path connectivity to communicate over the best signal—whether it's Wi-Fi or cellular. The cellular service will come from either AT&T or Verizon, depending on which carrier is stronger at your home. Just call or chat us to let us know if you have a preference.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Does my security system have a warranty?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Your system hardware is covered by a 2-year limited warranty. If anything breaks during the first two years, we'll replace it[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Take my system with me if I move to new home?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Yes. That's one of the advantages of a wireless self-installed system. Just take the devices down from your old home and place them in your new home. Once you have installed your system in the new location, just call or chat to let us know. Your monthly rate will remain the same unless you choose to add additional services.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can I get an additional system for my home?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Of course! Just call or chat with one of our security experts to get started.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What is professional monitoring?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]A professionally monitored system transmits alarm signals to an Alarm Response Center, a sophisticated 24/7 call center that can rapidly notify police, fire or medical authorities during any emergency. Around-the-clock professional monitoring is especially important because calling 911 on your cell phone won't connect you to the correct authorities unless you're currently located within their jurisdiction. The professionals in our monitoring center will alert the correct authorities no matter where you are.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How many months is the agreement?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Your agreement is for 36 months. item.title: HD-TVI Video Security System
item.content:encoded: Support Ultra-Long Continuous Recording and Backup By USB. DVR can be set to automatically overwrite the oldest internally stored footage or you can transfer those video files by USB to a memory stick or external hard drive. Be notified when there are unexpected movements. Smart notifications with image will be pushed to your smartphone via iPhone/Android App. You also can setup the Detection zone from your DVR to minimize false alarms. The free app Zosi Smart lets you see all of your cameras in one place. Check in on your home or business wherever you have an internet connection. Free App for Live View & Playback on Smart Devices with WiFi or 2G/3G/4G Anywhere Anytime. Smart Phone Support: iPhone, Android ,Ipad
item.excerpt:encoded: Get a sharp and crisp image day or night with the camera's automatic IR-cut filter. Up to 65ft night vision. Aluminum weatherproof housing, cameras can be used indoors and outdoors.

item.content:encoded: Rechargeable Batteries - Arlo Pro cameras include rechargeable batteries that support fast chargingFocus range (ST). item.excerpt:encoded: Works with Alexa for voice control (Alexa device sold separately). 100% Wire-free - Free of power cords and wiring hassles. Weather-resistant - Arlo Pro cameras are Weather-resistant so you can place them anywhere-indoors and out.

item.title: Home Security Door Alarm System
item.content:encoded: Our enthusiastic programmers develop WP6 APP to be extremely easy-install, easy-operation based on the variety of user experience & customer requirements. The APP allows you to control the whole security system anywhere with your IOS/Android Smartphone or tablet and receives warning notifications of the exact area when the alarm was triggered. Moreover, the APP has many humanization functions such as arming delay, clock, timing arming etc. WP6 home Alarm system kit includes 1x PIR Main Panel, 1x wireless PIR motion detector, 5x Door/window sensor, 2x Remote control, 1x AC adaptor, 1x user manual, and all backup battery and installation accessories. All sensors&remote control was connected with main panel already, each sensor is with label number for you to easy to tell. Super easy to install with included mounting mount and adhesive tape. No install fee, no contracts no monthly monitoring fee.
item.excerpt:encoded: Most cost-effective professional wireless security home alarm system kit with the easy APP! The built-in magnetic contact sensor and PIR motion sensor detect any forceful break-in to activate the alarm to deter potential intruders (0-120db), chime prompt, SOS emergency for home/business/office/child/disabled person safety protection. (Note: PIR detector is 8m, 110-degree field of view to cover day and night, NOT PET IMMUNITY TYPE).
